			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Another thing to add.  <BR>
<BR>
Down times for Druids at later levels:  With Root and DOT (which is my preferred method and leaves me with very little downtime) I have been getting a bubble an hour to a bubble every two hours throughout the 30's (level 35 not included).  At 39 I was moving at about a bubble every hour and a half.  I play it safe and make sure I always have enough mana for a get away and for a bad pull, so it could be faster (I med to full more than I probably should.).  In case anyone tells you differently, this is much faster than with a group (unless I decided to fight in Overthere).<BR>
<BR>
We are not the best class.  I have other characters including a Necro and an Enchanter.  Enchanters are nice.  Necros are awesome.  I still love playing my Druid because of all of the diversity and ability to get around.<BR>
<BR>
Snydarea
