	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				There is one principle that you must always remember as a Druid and this principle not only will keep you alive, but it will help you solo almost indefinately.<BR>
<BR>
IF YOU CAN SNARE IT, YOU CAN KILL IT.<BR>
<BR>
Druids do not get big burn spells or DOT's or BUF's or Heal's.  However, with the power of Snare, all of those other weaker abilities are at the proper mix and balance to handle any foe (any foe that can be Snared).<BR>
<BR>
As for soloing, this has not been a problem for me so far and all of my fellow Druid friends.  At 24, I really began learning the art of kiting.  This is a bit late in the game, but once this world opened up, my Druid experience became much more gratifying.  I do not particularly care to solo, but now I had something to do when I could not find a group.<BR>
<BR>
I began soloing Griffawns and Crags at 24.  Then I went to the Aviaks and began soloing them moving through the ranks of Egrets, Darters, Harriers, and Avocets.  At 30 I began soloing Griffennes, Giant Skeletons, and Cyclops.  At 33 I went to Kunark and started killing Burynai Minors, Dragoons, and occasional Hillocks.  At 34 I soloed my first HG.  It took forever and was not worth the time so I went back to Kunark and worked my way up through the ranks to Burynai Digmasters, Cenobites, Raiders, Whipcracks, Brutes, Ravenous, Hillocks, and Tumps.  At 38 I began killing Braes and Craigs and anything else that was still Blue to me in Frontier Mountains as well as killing Guards in West Commons, Griffins, Griffons, and the occasional Hill Giant.  At 39 I began dedicating more time to killing Hill Giants and began killing the Meadowgreen Centaurs in SK to pass the time.  I am now at 40 and HG are an easy kill without having to Run-Med-Kite.  I can kill 95% just on Snare and Burn.  Occasionally I still try to Root and DOT, but they still break Root a little too fast.<BR>
<BR>
There is lot to solo out there.  Kunark has many things for us to solo all the way up to 50.  Probably beyond this point, but I have not asked my friends that are into thier 50's.  If you want to wait a bit, you can still solo HG well into your 40's and make all of the money you will ever need.  Get bored with HG, there are tons of other things to solo including Guards in various zones, Spectres, Sand Giants, more Aviaks, OOT stuff, Guk...Too many to list.<BR>
<BR>
Kiting is what makes a Druid.  We are one with Nature and prefer to be in the company of the natural world and not others, even of our own kind.  We spend our lives solo and revere what nature has given us.  That is the credo and essence of being a Druid is all about.  Kiting is not just Cheap Power Leveling as some say.  It is a power we have by design.  Use it.  Let Snare be your best friend.  It just might save your life some day when you are OOM.  It might even save your parties life.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
